{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b35-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"109"},"text":"§ 109.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Major system","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b36-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this subtitle, the term “major system” means a combination of elements that will function together to produce the capabilities required to fulfill a mission need. These elements may include hardware, equipment, software, or a combination of hardware, equipment, and software, but do not include construction or other improvements to real property.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b37-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"System Deemed To Be Major System","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A system is deemed to be a major system if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b38-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Department of Defense is responsible for the system and the total expenditures for research, development, testing, and evaluation for the system are estimated to exceed $75,000,000 (based on fiscal year 1980 constant dollars) or the eventual total expenditure for procurement exceeds $300,000,000 (based on fiscal year 1980 constant dollars);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b39-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a civilian agency is responsible for the system and total expenditures for the system are estimated to exceed the greater of $750,000 (based on fiscal year 1980 constant dollars) or the dollar threshold for a major system established by the agency pursuant to Office of Management and Budget (OMB) Circular A–109, entitled “Major Systems Acquisitions”; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b3a-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2","identifier":"/us/usc/t41/s109/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the head of the agency responsible for the system designates the system a major system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id83b39b3b-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3680"},"text":"124 Stat. 3680","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id83b39b3c-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id83b39b3d-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id83b39b3e-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2"},"text":"\n","